{"parse":{"title":"Books on British railway accidents","pageid":5230786,"revid":835706157,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>\n\nThere are a number of <b>books on British railway accidents</b> which provide aid in the systematic study of the causes and effects of accidents, and their prevention.  There are common themes in many accidents (see <a href=\"/wiki/Classification_of_railway_accidents\" title=\"Classification of railway accidents\">Classification</a>). Key books are listed here to avoid repeating them for each individual accident.\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/wiki/Doyen\" title=\"Doyen\">doyen</a> is <a href=\"/wiki/L._T._C._Rolt\" title=\"L. T. C. Rolt\">L. T. C. Rolt</a>'s <i>Red for Danger</i>, first published in 1956, which takes a wide-ranging overview of over 100 accidents.  Most other books concentrate on a smaller number of specific accidents, described in more detail.  O.S. Nock's \"Historic Railway Disasters\" combines both approaches, with individual chapters on especially significant accidents such as <a href=\"/wiki/Armagh_rail_disaster\" title=\"Armagh rail disaster\">Armagh</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Quintinshill_rail_crash\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Quintinshill rail crash\">Quintinshill</a>.  For accidents in the last 30 years and modern operating practice, Stanley Hall's four books are particularly good.  Apart from Schneider and Mase (1968/1970) and Faith (2001), all the books below are confined to British accidents.\n</p><p>The list below does not include books on individual accidents; for these, see <a href=\"/wiki/Tay_Bridge_disaster\" title=\"Tay Bridge disaster\">Tay Bridge</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Quintinshill_rail_crash\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Quintinshill rail crash\">Quintinshill</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Harrow_and_Wealdstone_rail_crash\" title=\"Harrow and Wealdstone rail crash\">Harrow</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Hixon_rail_crash\" title=\"Hixon rail crash\">Hixon</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Moorgate_tube_crash\" title=\"Moorgate tube crash\">Moorgate</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Lockington_rail_crash\" title=\"Lockington rail crash\">Lockington</a>.\n</p><p>An extremely valuable source now on the Internet is the Railways Archive compilation of official Railway Inspectorate Accident Reports - see \"External Links\" below.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Key_books\">Key books</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Books_on_British_railway_accidents&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Key books\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Faith, Nicholas (2001). <i>Derail: Why Trains Crash</i> (2nd ed.). Channel 4 Books. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-7522-1987-1\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-7522-1987-1\">0-7522-1987-1</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Derail%3A+Why+Trains+Crash&amp;rft.edition=2nd&amp;rft.pub=Channel+4+Books&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.isbn=0-7522-1987-1&amp;rft.aulast=Faith&amp;rft.aufirst=Nicholas&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABooks+on+British+railway+accidents\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> First published 1998 to accompany the Channel 4 series.  An overall survey like Rolt's, but covering worldwide accidents.</li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Hall, Stanley (1987). <i>Danger Signals: an investigation into modern railway accidents</i>. Ian Allan. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-7110-1704-2\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-7110-1704-2\">0-7110-1704-2</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Danger+Signals%3A+an+investigation+into+modern+railway+accidents&amp;rft.pub=Ian+Allan&amp;rft.date=1987&amp;rft.isbn=0-7110-1704-2&amp;rft.aulast=Hall&amp;rft.aufirst=Stanley&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABooks+on+British+railway+accidents\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span>  A broad survey, concentrating especially on accidents in the 20 years up to 1986, especially those caused by drivers' and signalmen's errors.</li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Hall, Stanley (1991). <i>Danger on the Line</i>. Ian Allan. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-7110-1872-3\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-7110-1872-3\">0-7110-1872-3</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Danger+on+the+Line&amp;rft.pub=Ian+Allan&amp;rft.date=1991&amp;rft.isbn=0-7110-1872-3&amp;rft.aulast=Hall&amp;rft.aufirst=Stanley&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABooks+on+British+railway+accidents\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span>  Covers Clapham Junction, Purley, Glasgow Bellgrove and a wide range of other accidents, e.g. track problems, fires, staff fatalities.</li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Hall, Stanley (1999). <i>Hidden Dangers</i>. Ian Allan. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-7137-1973-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-7137-1973-7\">0-7137-1973-7</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Hidden+Dangers&amp;rft.pub=Ian+Allan&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.isbn=0-7137-1973-7&amp;rft.aulast=Hall&amp;rft.aufirst=Stanley&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABooks+on+British+railway+accidents\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> Covers the period 1989-97 including Cowden, Newton and Southall.</li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Hall, Stanley (2003). <i>Beyond Hidden Dangers: Railway Safety into the 21st Century</i>. Ian Allan. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-7110-2915-6\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-7110-2915-6\">0-7110-2915-6</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Beyond+Hidden+Dangers%3A+Railway+Safety+into+the+21st+Century&amp;rft.pub=Ian+Allan&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.isbn=0-7110-2915-6&amp;rft.aulast=Hall&amp;rft.aufirst=Stanley&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABooks+on+British+railway+accidents\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span>.  Includes Ladbroke Grove, Hatfield, Potters Bar, Great Heck (Selby).</li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Hamilton., J.A.B. (1967). <i>British Railway Accidents of the 20th Century (reprinted 1987 as Disaster down the Line)</i>. George Allen and Unwin / Javelin Books. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-7137-1973-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-7137-1973-7\">0-7137-1973-7</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=British+Railway+Accidents+of+the+20th+Century+%28reprinted+1987+as+Disaster+down+the+Line%29.&amp;rft.pub=George+Allen+and+Unwin+%2F+Javelin+Books&amp;rft.date=1967&amp;rft.isbn=0-7137-1973-7&amp;rft.aulast=Hamilton.&amp;rft.aufirst=J.A.B.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABooks+on+British+railway+accidents\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> Covers 27 accidents between 1905 and 1962. Particularly good on the human factor and psychological reasons behind accidents.</li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Nock, O.S. (1980). <i>Historic Railway Disasters</i> (2nd ed.). Ian Allan.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Historic+Railway+Disasters&amp;rft.edition=2nd&amp;rft.pub=Ian+Allan&amp;rft.date=1980&amp;rft.aulast=Nock&amp;rft.aufirst=O.S.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABooks+on+British+railway+accidents\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span>  First published 1966, another well-written classic.</li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Rolt, L.T.C. (1956). <i>Red for Danger</i>. Bodley Head / David and Charles / Pan Books.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Red+for+Danger&amp;rft.pub=Bodley+Head+%2F+David+and+Charles+%2F+Pan+Books&amp;rft.date=1956&amp;rft.aulast=Rolt&amp;rft.aufirst=L.T.C.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABooks+on+British+railway+accidents\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span>  An excellent overview of accidents up to 1957, in fine writing style. An early reviewer wrote, \"At the risk of being thought callous, one must praise Mr Rolt for making death and disaster most attractive reading\". Several revised and updated editions published (1960, 1966, 1976, 1982).  Later editions have material added by G.M. Kichenside.</li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Schneider, Ascanio; Armand Mase (1968). <i>Katastrophen auf Schienen. (In German)</i>. Orell Fussli Verlag.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Katastrophen+auf+Schienen.+%28In+German%29&amp;rft.pub=Orell+Fussli+Verlag&amp;rft.date=1968&amp;rft.aulast=Schneider&amp;rft.aufirst=Ascanio&amp;rft.au=Armand+Mase&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABooks+on+British+railway+accidents\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Schneider, Ascanio; Armand Mase (1970). <i>Railway Accidents of (Great Britain and) Europe.  Translated from German (book above) by E.L. Dellow</i>. David and Charles. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-7153-4791-8\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-7153-4791-8\">0-7153-4791-8</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Railway+Accidents+of+%28Great+Britain+and%29+Europe.++Translated+from+German+%28book+above%29+by+E.L.+Dellow&amp;rft.pub=David+and+Charles&amp;rft.date=1970&amp;rft.isbn=0-7153-4791-8&amp;rft.aulast=Schneider&amp;rft.aufirst=Ascanio&amp;rft.au=Armand+Mase&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABooks+on+British+railway+accidents\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span>  Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Classification_of_railway_accidents\" title=\"Classification of railway accidents\">classification</a> and numerous European accidents.</li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Vaughan, Adrian (1989). <i>Obstruction Danger</i>. Guild Publishing. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-85260-055-1\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1-85260-055-1\">1-85260-055-1</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Obstruction+Danger&amp;rft.pub=Guild+Publishing&amp;rft.date=1989&amp;rft.isbn=1-85260-055-1&amp;rft.aulast=Vaughan&amp;rft.aufirst=Adrian&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABooks+on+British+railway+accidents\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span>  Written by a former signalman, with an interesting selection including some less well-known mishaps.</li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\"><i>British Railway Disasters</i>. Ian Allan. 1996. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-7110-2470-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-7110-2470-7\">0-7110-2470-7</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=British+Railway+Disasters&amp;rft.pub=Ian+Allan&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.isbn=0-7110-2470-7&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABooks+on+British+railway+accidents\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> covers 47 accidents between 1876 and 1991 with many photographs.</li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Vaughan, Adrian (2000). <i>Tracks to Disaster</i>. Ian Allan. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-7110-2731-5\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-7110-2731-5\">0-7110-2731-5</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Tracks+to+Disaster&amp;rft.pub=Ian+Allan&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.isbn=0-7110-2731-5&amp;rft.aulast=Vaughan&amp;rft.aufirst=Adrian&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABooks+on+British+railway+accidents\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> 19 modern accidents in the period 1975-97.  Like his previous book, contains some trenchant comments on railway management.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Books_on_British_railway_accidents&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.railwaysarchive.co.uk/listing.php?PHPSESSID=6a3f8d82df26a7e7b93812055ff97a3f&amp;showSearch=true&amp;sortKey=date&amp;sortDirection=ASC&amp;text=&amp;startYear=all&amp;endYear=all&amp;event=all&amp;development=all&amp;category=4&amp;author=all&amp;publisher=all&amp;published=yes&amp;submit=Go\">Railway Archive- Accident Report</a>.</li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://catskillarchive.com/rrextra/wkbktoc.Html\">Early railways in the UK and USA by Charles Adams (published in 1879)</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.rail-reg.gov.uk/server/show/nav.1112\">Office of the Railway Regulator</a> Reports on major incidents</li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20080915212426/http://www.raib.gov.uk/publications/index.cfm\">UK Rail Accident Investigation Branch</a> Publications - Covers the period from  2006 onward. Note as well as major accidents there are reports on relatively minor incidents.</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1262\nCached time: 20180910084618\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.116 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.136 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 486/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 16398/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 256/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive parser function count: 2/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.070/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 3.42 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  115.389      1 -total\n 71.65%   82.682     13 Template:Cite_book\n 23.45%  